com.codepoetics.fluvius.api.history

Interface FlowHistory<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type to which the flow's event data has been serialised.

    public interface FlowHistory<T>
    Represents the entire history of a flow's execution.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      List<FlowEvent<T>> getEventHistory()
      Get the event history of this flow's execution, consisting of all the FlowEvents that have been emitted during execution.
      UUID getFlowId()
      Get the id of the flow to which this history belongs.
      TraceMap getTraceMap()
      Get a TraceMap representing all of the possible execution paths for this flow.
      <V> List<V> getTranslatedEventHistory(FlowEventTranslator<T,V> translator)
      Get a translated event history, translated using the provided FlowEventTranslator.
